{% extends "layouts/app-layout.njk" %}

{% set pageTitle = "Search input" %}
{% set pageSection = "Design system" %}
{% set subSection = "Components" %}
{% set pageDescription = "Use a search input to help users find content by entering a word, phrase or part of a word." %}
{% set theme = "Form elements" %}
{% set dateUpdated = "May 2026" %}
{% set backlog_issue_id = "587" %}

{% block beforeContent %}
  {% include "design-system/components/_breadcrumb.njk" %}
{% endblock %}

{% block bodyContent %}

  {{ designExample({
    group: "components",
    item: "search-input",
    type: "default"
  }) }}

  <h2>When to use search input</h2>
  <p>Use a search input when users need to find specific content quickly by entering a word, phrase or part of a word.</p>
  <p>Search can be enabled in the <a href="/design-system/components/header">header component</a>, use this to provide a global search.</p>

  <h2>When not to use search input</h2>
  <p>Do not rely on search in place of clear navigation.</p>

  <h2>How to use search input</h2>
  <p>The search input can be large or small, depending on the context of the page. For example, a dedicated search page may want a large size input.</p>
  {{ designExample({
    group: "components",
    item: "search-input",
    type: "large"
  }) }}

  <p>The search input shows a cross icon once a character has been typed, allowing users to clear the input and start a new search.</p>
  <p>If searching by a unique identifier, for example an NHS number, users should be taken directly to the matching result's page. If the search does not return a unique result, users should be presented with a results page.</p>
  <p>The search button can include a text label for specific use cases, for example "Find".</p>

  <p>Depending on the hierarchy of the page, the search input can use a secondary button.</p>
  {{ designExample({
    group: "components",
    item: "search-input",
    type: "secondary-button"
  }) }}

  <h2>Research</h2>
  <p>If you've used a search input in your service, please share your user research findings.</p>

{% endblock %}
